Module simplifier
Package ie.gmit.dip

Interface AbstractConvertible<T,​U,​R>

  • Type Parameters:
    T - a generic type for the convertible object.
    U - a generic type for the converted object.
    R - a generic type for the converters used to carry out conversion.
    All Known Implementing Classes:
    ConvertibleString
    public interface AbstractConvertible<T,​U,​R>
    The interface AbstractConvertible is an abstract base type which defines the basic functionality expected in a more specialized hierarchy of convertible types, that is, something of type T is convertible to a type U, by a converter of type R.
    Since:
    JavaSE-11
    Version:
    1.0
    Author:
    Kieran P. Somers

      • setConverters

        void setConverters​(R converters)
        Method which allows converters of type R to be defined. This allows for a convertible to undergo multiple conversions if a Collection of converters are provided. The Collection can be ordered or unordered, the user should be specific depending on the use case.
        Parameters:
        converters - a single converter, or multiple converters, used to carry out conversion.

      • convert

        void convert()
        The key method for a convertible is the convert method. The details of conversion are handled by any specific concrete type that implements this interface.
